description:
refactor code to work like like: the recommended approach for sharing TypeScript types between server and client code in Nuxt 4.

Solution:
1. Create a shared types directory at project root (e.g., shared/types or packages/shared/types)
2. Put common TypeScript interfaces and types there (e.g., ApiResponse, User, DTOs)
3. Configure TS path aliases in tsconfig.json so both server and client can import from the same path

Example tsconfig.json configuration:
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "baseUrl": ".",
    "paths": {
      "@shared/*": ["shared/types/*"]
    }
  }
}

This avoids duplicating type definitions and ensures consistency across the full stack.
